@startuml
!pragma layout smetana
title Thesis workflow — from text to validated consensus simulation

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

[Text records\n( e.g. Working Papers + Final Reports,\nSecretariat archive, English)] as INPUT

package "Preprocessing" {
  [Clean, segment, filter] as PRE
}

package "Chapter 1 — Support Layer" {
  [Topic discovery (BERTopic) +\nrelevance gating +\nNLI stance contrast +\naggregation] as CH1
}

package "Chapter 2 — Opposition Layer\n& External Validation" {
  [Opposition extraction from\nText +\noutcome prediction] as CH2
}

package "Chapter 3 — Simulation Layer" {
  [MARL negotiation environment\n(veto-player consensus game)] as CH3
}

[Outputs:\nreproduced historical consensus,\ndecision-rule counterfactuals] as OUT

INPUT --> PRE
PRE --> CH1

CH1 --> CH2 : Support tensor (S)

CH2 --> CH3 : Signed preference structure\n(S + opposition tensor (O))

GARD --> CH3 : out-of-sample\nvalidation + counterfactuals
CH3 --> OUT

note bottom of CH1
  What: directional, signed measure of national
  policy support per topic over time.
  Implemented (preliminary infrastructure).
end note
note bottom of CH2
  What: who opposes which proposals, from
  summarised debate; combined with S into a
  signed preference network. Validates both
  layers by predicting real ATCM outcomes.
end note
note bottom of CH3
  What: agents = Parties holding a veto; state =
  S + O; reward = support - opposition - cost.
  Tests whether extracted preferences reproduce
  consensus and its failures. Proof of concept.
end note
@enduml
